-- China's Stocks Fluctuate as Coal, Consumer Companies Gain, Brokers Slide
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-22T05:22:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/china-s-stocks-fluctuate-as-coal-consumer-companies-gain-brokers-slide.html
China’s stocks fluctuated as coal
producers and consumer companies gained on an improving earnings
outlook while banks and brokerages slid on concern faster
inflation may push the central bank to increase interest rates
further.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, rose 5.18, or 0.2 percent, to 2,988.72
as of 1:18 p.m. after falling as much as 1 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  